The paper discusses the use of diversity combining in RF energy harvesting systems, which involves signal processing techniques to combine multiple signals to improve the overall performance. This topic is closely related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI), as well as control systems (cs.SY) and electromagnetics (cs.EM). Additionally, the paper may also fall under the category of computer architecture and embedded systems (cs.AR) as it discusses the power consumption of the diversity combining process.
